The paper deals with wireless distributed computing, which involves communication and information theory (cs.IT) as well as networking and communication protocols (cs.NI). The proposed framework aims to reduce communication bandwidth, which is a key issue in distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses optimization and coding schemes, which are relevant to control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
